<body>

    <!-- Header Section -->
    <header>
        <nav class="container">
            <div class="logo">Neurodivergent Guide</div>
            <div class="nav-links">
                <a href="#strengths">Strengths</a>
                <a href="#support">Support</a>
                <a href="#strategies">Strategies</a>
                <a href="#resources">Resources</a>
            </div>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="container">

        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section class="hero-section">
            <h1 class="gradient-text">A Guide to Supporting Your Neurodivergent Self</h1>
            <p>A framework of recommendations to support an individual with an AuDHD (Autism + ADHD) profile in building a life that honors their neurotype, leverages their strengths, and provides scaffolding for areas of challenge.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Strengths Section -->
        <section id="strengths">
            <h2 class="section-title">üß† Acknowledging Your Strengths</h2>
            <div class="strengths-grid">
                <div class="strength-card border-violet">
                    <h3 class="text-violet">Deep Focus & Passionate Interests</h3>
                    <p>Your ability to immerse yourself in topics is a powerful asset that allows for the development of expert-level knowledge.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strength-card border-sky">
                    <h3 class="text-sky">Pattern Recognition & Systemizing</h3>
                    <p>Many neurodivergent individuals excel at seeing connections and systems that others miss, making them natural problem-solvers.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strength-card border-teal">
                    <h3 class="text-teal">Honesty, Loyalty, & Strong Moral Compass</h3>
                    <p>A preference for direct communication and a deep sense of justice are common traits that foster reliable and principled relationships.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strength-card border-lime">
                    <h3 class="text-lime">Creativity & Innovative Thinking</h3>
                    <p>Your mind is likely a wellspring of ideas, capable of making rapid, novel connections that lead to exceptional creativity.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strength-card border-rose">
                    <h3 class="text-rose">Resilience & Adaptability</h3>
                    <p>Navigating a world not built for your brain style fosters incredible resilience and perseverance.</p>
                </div>
                 <div class="strength-card border-orange">
                    <h3 class="text-orange">Heightened Sensory Experience</h3>
                    <p>While sensitivities can be a challenge, they can also lead to a richer, more detailed, and nuanced appreciation of the world.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Support Section -->
        <section id="support" class="support-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">ü§ù Building Your Support System</h2>
            <div>
                <div class="support-category">
                    <h3>I. Therapeutic & Clinical Support</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>Individual Therapy:</b> Engage with a provider who is explicitly neurodiversity-affirming and trauma-informed. Look for person-centered, validating approaches. Resources like Zocdoc and Psychology Today can help.</li>
                        <li><b>Specialized Treatment:</b> If co-occurring OCD is present, consider Exposure and Response Prevention (ERP) adapted for a neurodivergent profile.</li>
                        <li><b>Medication Management:</b> Consult a knowledgeable psychiatrist to discuss options for ADHD that may improve executive functioning and emotional regulation.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="support-category">
                    <h3>II. Systems, Advocacy, & Community Support</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>Apply for Public Services:</b> Investigate eligibility for Supplemental Security Income (SSI), Medicaid, and state-level Developmental Disability Services (like Regional Centers in CA).</li>
                        <li><b>Know Your Rights:</b> Familiarize yourself with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and state-specific laws (like the Lanterman Act in CA).</li>
                        <li><b>Connect with Peers:</b> Seek out online or in-person peer support groups for neurodivergent adults to reduce isolation and find validation.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Strategies Section -->
        <section id="strategies">
            <h2 class="section-title">üí° Self-Advocacy & Well-being Strategies</h2>
            <div class="strategies-grid">
                <div class="strategy-card">
                    <h3>Honor Your Sensory System</h3>
                    <p>Proactively create comfortable environments. Use tools like tinted lenses (e.g., FL-41), noise-canceling headphones, blackout curtains, and weighted blankets to manage sensory input.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strategy-card">
                    <h3>Authentic Communication</h3>
                    <p>Consciously reduce masking in safe relationships. Practice explicitly stating your needs and boundaries. Connect with others on your own terms in ways that feel energizing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strategy-card">
                    <h3>Physical Well-being</h3>
                    <p>Engage in regular physical movement that feels good to your body. Explore sustainable nutritional shifts, like focusing on adequate protein intake.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="strategy-card">
                    <h3>Vocational & Independent Living</h3>
                    <p>Explore state vocational training services. Use external aids like visual timers, checklists, and apps to support executive functioning and financial planning.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Resources Section -->
        <section id="resources" class="resources-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">üìö Psychoeducation & Further Learning</h2>
            <div>
                <div class="resources-grid">
                    <div>
                        <h3>üîó Recommended Websites</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><a href="https://neurodivergentinsights.com" target="_blank">Neurodivergent Insights</a></li>
                            <li><a href="https://autisticadvocacy.org" target="_blank">Autistic Self Advocacy Network (ASAN)</a></li>
                            <li><a href="https://chadd.org" target="_blank">CHADD</a></li>
                            <li><a href="https://www.pdasociety.org.uk" target="_blank">PDA Society</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>üìñ Selected Books</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><i>Unmasking Autism</i> by Devon Price, Ph.D.</li>
                            <li><i>NeuroTribes</i> by Steve Silberman</li>
                            <li><i>Divergent Mind</i> by Jenara Nerenberg</li>
                            <li><i>Sincerely, Your Autistic Child</i> by AWN</li>
                            <li><i>How to Keep House While Drowning</i> by KC Davis, LPC</li>
                            <li><i>Taking Charge of ADHD</i> by Russell A. Barkley, Ph.D.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer>
        <div class="container">
            <p>&copy; 2025 Neurodivergent Guide. A resource for understanding and affirmation.</p>
